I have a tech question for you.
{p} {p}
I have several amigas, one of which is an A2K full Tower with 030/25
Vector Accellorator (IVS). 8MB on the accellerator, and a 2081 Ram
board with 4MB.  CV64/3D gfx card 4MB with cybergfx, 1GB SCSI hard
drive, SCSI Zip drive, and SCSI CDRom drive.
{p} {p}
Problems is this:  Accellerator boots fine in 030 mode, and is
supposed to be able to boot into 68000 mode, but won't.  68000 chip is
a known good one.
{p} {p}
Thanks,
{p} {p}
